lines.text: The snowflake once fell on my nose, now flying backwards to last winter
I realize that hellos are goodbyes the moment I softly let go of your hand
Wings of fruit, the trembling branches
A soul for a soul bound to soar
To the very edge of the staring ocean
And if, and if, I mean to fall apart
I will be set where you are for all time
But oh yeah
May your path be clear
May you get aware, dreams are all crystallized
Will, please, crack a little smile
You belong in this world you've chosen as your own
Don't worry, I'm well aware that
All snowflakes melt in the end
Witches sigh on warmth and hope of spring
So Elden's flamboyant to that good night
Bove, oh yes
May your path be clear
May you get aware
Dreams are all crystallized with
Please, crack a little smile
You'll be alone
In this world you've chosen
As your own
Tiny, it's such a dazzling riddle
Guess I'll spend my whole life unraveling
The world where my curse made everything I have
I never regret, wouldn't have it any other way
Cause those who trace their light on their lonely roads
Will find their destination in the cosmos
Meeting you in the swirling snowfalls
The most beautiful thing ever happened to me
